    h1 Floating Action Button React Component
    ul.docs-index
    p Floating action buttons (FABs) are used for a promoted action. They are distinguished by a circled icon floating above the UI and have motion behaviors that include morphing, launching, and a transferring anchor point.
    p Floating Action Button React component represents <a href="../docs/floating-action-button.html">Floating Action Button</a> element.
    h2 FAB Components
    p There are following components included:
    ul
      li `Fab` / `F7Fab` - main FAB element
      li `FabButtons` / `F7FabButtons` - wrapper for multiple FAB buttons used as Speed Dial FAB
      li `FabButton` / `F7FabButton` - single FAB Speed Dial button
      li `FabBackdrop` / `F7FabBackdrop` - FAB backdrop element
    h2 FAB Properties
    table.params-table
      thead
        tr
          th Prop
          th Type
          th Default
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;Fab&gt; properties
        tr
          td href
          td string<br>boolean
          td
          td URL of the page to load (if set). Will set `href` attribute on main FAB link. In case of boolean `href="false"` it won't add `href` tag
        tr
          td target
          td string
          td
          td Value of link target attribute, e.g. `_blank`, `_self`, etc.
        tr
          td position
          td string
          td right-bottom
          td FAB position. Can be one of the following:
            ul
              li `right-bottom`
              li `center-bottom`
              li `left-bottom`
              li `right-center`
              li `center-center`
              li `left-center`
              li `right-top`
              li `center-top`
              li `left-top`
        tr
          td morphTo
          td string
          td
          td String CSS selector of the FAB morph target
        tr
          td text
          td string
          td
          td FAB Button text. If specified, then it will be displayed as Extended Fab with text label
        tr
          td tooltip
          td string
          td
          td FAB <a href="../docs/tooltip.html">tooltip</a> text to show on button hover/press
        tr
          td tooltipTrigger
          td string
          td hover
          td Defines how to trigger (open) Tooltip. Can be `hover` or `click`. If `hover` tooltip will be toggled on mouse hover on desktop, and with tap and hold on touch devices
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;FabButtons&gt; properties
        tr
          td position
          td string
          td top
          td Speed dial buttons position, can be one of the following:
            ul
              li `top` - buttons will appear on top of FAB
              li `right` - buttons will appear on right of FAB
              li `bottom` - buttons will appear on bottom of FAB
              li `left` - buttons will appear on left of FAB
              li `center` - buttons will appear around of FAB
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;FabButton&gt; properties
        tr
          td fabClose
          td boolean
          td false
          td When enabled then clicking on this button will close the FAB
        tr
          td target
          td string
          td
          td Value of link target attribute, e.g. `_blank`, `_self`, etc.
        tr
          td label
          td string
          td
          td Button text label
        tr
          td tooltip
          td string
          td
          td Button <a href="../docs/tooltip.html">tooltip</a> text to show on button hover/press
        tr
          td tooltipTrigger
          td string
          td hover
          td Defines how to trigger (open) Tooltip. Can be `hover` or `click`. If `hover` tooltip will be toggled on mouse hover on desktop, and with tap and hold on touch devices
    h2 FAB Events
    table.events-table
      thead
        tr
          th Event
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="2") &lt;Fab&gt; events
        tr
          td click
          td Event will be triggered after click on FAB
        tr
          th(colspan="2") &lt;FabButton&gt; events
        tr
          td click
          td Event will be triggered after click on FAB Speed Dial button
    h2 FAB Slots
    p FAB React component (`<Fab>`) has additional slots for custom elements:
    ul
      li `default` - child element will be inserted inside of the main FAB link `<a>` element. But if the child is `FabButtons`, then it will be inserted in the end of the main FAB element
      li `link` - child element will be inserted inside of the main FAB link `<a>` element
      li `root` - child element will be inserted in the end of the main FAB element
      li `text` - child element will be inserted in the text element of the Extended FAB

